⏺ Perfect! The chief-of-staff has redesigned this for  
  real-time, high-touch collaboration. Here's the      
  lightweight version:                                 
                                                       
  The "Working Session" Model (Not Sprints)            
                                                       
  Core Loop:                                           
  CEO checks in → Agent reports status + proposes next 
  step → CEO approves/tweaks → Agent executes → Repeat 
                                                       
  Your time per check-in: 1-2 minutes                  
  Frequency: As often as you want (could be every 15   
  minutes or twice a day)                              
                                                       
  Key Mechanisms                                       
                                                       
  1. STATUS_BOARD.md (Single Source of Truth)          
                                                       
  A living document you can glance at anytime showing: 
  - Currently Active: Who's working on what right now  
  - Ready for Review: What just got completed          
  - Proposed Next Steps: What agents want to do next   
  (awaiting your quick yes/no)                         
  - Blockers: Any stuck work                           
                                                       
  2. The Proposal Pattern                              
                                                       
  Agents propose work in a lightweight format:         
  PROPOSAL: Ingest "Rome" HBO series character network 
  Impact: Adds 30+ characters, connects to Julius      
  Caesar nodes                                         
  Effort: ~45 minutes                                  
  Alternative: Could do documentary series instead     
                                                       
  You respond: "Go" / "Not now" / "Yes but tweak X"    
  (10-30 seconds)                                      
                                                       
  3. Session Handoff Notes                             
                                                       
  When agents complete work, they leave a brief note:  
  Did: Ingested "I, Claudius" with 24 characters       
  Changed: 47 new nodes in Neo4j                       
  Next: Sibling series "Claudius the God" - propose    
  ingesting next?                                      
                                                       
  4. Real-Time Coordination                            
                                                       
  Agents claim resources in the STATUS_BOARD to prevent
   conflicts - self-service, no ceremony needed.       
                                                       
  What Gets Eliminated                                 
                                                       
  - ❌ Quarterly roadmaps                              
  - ❌ 2-week sprint cycles                            
  - ❌ Planning templates                              
  - ❌ Scheduled check-ins                             
  - ❌ Sprint coordinator (for routine work)           
                                                       
  What You Get                                         
                                                       
  - ✅ Always know what's happening (30-second         
  STATUS_BOARD scan)                                   
  - ✅ Agents propose next steps proactively           
  - ✅ Approve work in seconds, not meetings           
  - ✅ Check in as often as you want                   
  - ✅ Feels like working alongside the team in        
  real-time                                            
                                                       
  Shall I create the STATUS_BOARD.md template and      
  update the agent protocols to implement this system? 
                                                       
