⏺ Yes, absolutely! CHRONOS_LOG.md and the archive      
  continue to serve an important purpose, but with a   
  narrower, more focused scope:                        
                                                       
  The Three-Tier Documentation System                  
                                                       
  1. STATUS_BOARD.md (Real-Time)                       
                                                       
  - What's happening RIGHT NOW                         
  - Currently active work, proposals awaiting your     
  approval, completions ready for review               
  - You check this multiple times per day (30-second   
  scans)                                               
  - Gets rotated/cleaned regularly (current state only)
                                                       
  2. Session Handoff Notes (Routine Work)              
                                                       
  - Lives in STATUS_BOARD.md (accumulates until rotated
   ~weekly)                                            
  - Brief records of completed routine work            
  - Example: "Ingested 'Rome' HBO series - 30          
  characters, 47 new nodes"                            
  - Other agents read these to understand what just    
  shipped                                              
                                                       
  3. CHRONOS_LOG.md (Major Milestones Only)            
                                                       
  - Significant achievements and architectural         
  decisions                                            
  - Still rotates to archive when >3 entries           
  - Reserved for truly important events                
                                                       
  What qualifies for CHRONOS_LOG:                      
  - ✅ Major feature completions ("Implemented full    
  Wikidata integration")                               
  - ✅ Significant data milestones ("Ingested complete 
  Shakespeare filmography - 150+ works")               
  - ✅ Architectural decisions ("Migrated to           
  canonical_id for all entities")                      
  - ✅ Infrastructure changes ("Deployed CI/CD         
  pipeline")                                           
                                                       
  What uses handoff notes instead:                     
  - ❌ Routine ingestions ("Added 'Rome' HBO series")  
  - ❌ Small bug fixes ("Fixed typo in loading state") 
  - ❌ Polish work ("Improved button hover states")    
                                                       
  This keeps CHRONOS_LOG as your project history and   
  learning archive while STATUS_BOARD handles real-time
   operational visibility.                             
                                                       
  I've created both documents:                         
  - docs/STATUS_BOARD.md - Your real-time dashboard    
  - docs/WORKING_SESSION_PROTOCOL.md - Complete agent  
  workflow guide                                       
                                                       
  Ready to start using this system?                    
                                                       
